columns.description: The maximum number of commercial fiber internet service providers reported to be available per census block by council district.

columns.name: Public Computer Center Count
columns.description: Total Number of Public Computer Centers

columns.name: Workstations in PCCs
columns.description: Number of computer workstations, defined as desktop or laptop computers, available for public use at the center

columns.name: Avg training hrs per week in PCCs
columns.description: Average number of hours per week that the center provides digital literacy training programs.

columns.name: Public Wi-Fi Count
columns.description: Indicates the number of public Wi-Fi access points within the specified NTA.

columns.description: Poles that the City has reserved for use for the Mobile Telecommunications Franchise, without equipment installed.

columns.name: Pole with Equipment Installed by Mobile Telecom Franchise

columns.name: Density of Poles Reserved and with Equipment Installed for Mobile Telecom Franchise
columns.description: Total poles, reserved by Mobile Telecom Franchisee with or without  equipment installed, per square mile within the district.
